# Cargo build output — regenerated by `cargo build`, never committed.
/target
**/target

# Self-hosted engine, compiled from dart/self_host/engine.ball.json by
# `cargo run -p ball-engine-regen` (issue #39). Git-ignored like the C++
# self-host's engine_rt.cpp: it is a ~19k-line generated artifact that does not
# yet build through ball-compiler (gated behind the off-by-default `self_host`
# feature), so committing it would only add churn. CI/consumers regenerate it.
engine/src/compiled_engine.rs

# Self-hosted CLI core, compiled from dart/self_host/cli.ball.json by
# `cargo run -p ball-cli-regen` (issue #365). Git-ignored like
# compiled_engine.rs above: it is a generated artifact behind the
# off-by-default `cli_core` feature (rust/cli/Cargo.toml), so committing it
# would only add churn. CI/consumers regenerate it.
cli/src/compiled_cli.rs

# Build artifact copied/generated into the worktree by the regenerator's
# input; not part of the Rust sources.
build_errors*.txt
